#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid "Build Plugin"
msgstr "Vtičnik za izdelavo"

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:584 plugins.docbook:790 plugins.docbook:859
#: plugins.docbook:907 plugins.docbook:923 plugins.docbook:1093
#: plugins.docbook:1399 plugins.docbook:1596 plugins.docbook:2017
#: plugins.docbook:3083 plugins.docbook:3431 plugins.docbook:3751
#: plugins.docbook:3869
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:586
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Build plugin allows you to run actions like build, clean and compile on "
"a project. You can also automatically run the generated applications. The "
"plugin basically gives you a way to configure sets of commands to run and it "
"can parse the output for links to files and specific lines and columns in "
"those files. So even if the plugin is originally created for compiling C/C++ "
"and mostly tested with it, the plugin can also be useful for other purposes "
"and languages."
msgstr ""
"Vtičnik Build vam omogoča izvajanje dejanj, kot so gradnja, čiščenje in "
"prevajanje v projektu. Ustvarjene aplikacije lahko tudi samodejno zaženete. "
"Vtičnik vam v bistvu omogoča način konfiguriranja naborov ukazov za "
"izvajanje in lahko razčleni izhod za povezave do datotek ter določene "
"vrstice in stolpce v teh datotekah. Tudi če je bil vtičnik prvotno ustvarjen "
"za prevajanje C/C++ in večinoma preizkušen z njim, je lahko vtičnik uporaben "
"tudi za druge namene in jezike."

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:596
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Build Plugin"
msgstr "Uporaba vtičnika Build"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:598
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Build plugin adds a <guilabel>Build</guilabel> tool view at the bottom "
"and a <guimenu>Build</guimenu> menu on the menu bar. The tool view can be "
"used to select and configure build targets, while the menu and its shortcuts "
"can be used to select and execute the configured shell commands."
msgstr ""
"Vtičnik Build doda pogled orodja <guilabel>Build</guilabel> na dnu in meni "
"<guimenu>Izgradi</guimenu> v menijski vrstici. Pogled orodij je mogoče "
"uporabiti za izbiro in konfiguracijo ciljev gradnje, medtem ko je meni in "
"njegove bližnjice mogoče uporabiti za izbiro in izvajanje konfiguriranih "
"ukazov lupine (shell)."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: plugins.docbook:604
#, no-c-format
msgid "Build Output"
msgstr "Build izhod"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:610
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <guilabel>Build</guilabel> tool view has two static tabs:"
msgstr "Pogled orodja <guilabel>Build</guilabel> ima dva statična zavihka:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:613
#, no-c-format
msgid "Target Settings"
msgstr "Ciljne nastavitve"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:614
#, no-c-format
msgid "Output"
msgstr "Izhod"

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:618
#, no-c-format
msgid "Target Settings tab"
msgstr "Zavihek Nastavitve cilja"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:620
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The target settings tab can be used to configure various build targets and "
"define target sets."
msgstr ""
"Zavihek z nastavitvami cilja lahko uporabite za konfiguracijo različnih "
"ciljev gradnje in definiranje naborov ciljev."

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A target-set is a group of commands that can be run in a specified working "
"directory. Target sets can be added under either <guilabel>Projects</"
"guilabel> or <guilabel>Session</guilabel>. The custom target-sets added "
"under <guilabel>Projects</guilabel> are stored in a <guilabel>.kateproject."
"build</guilabel> file in the project root directory and are restored when "
"the project is re-opened. The target-sets added under <guilabel>Session</"
"guilabel> are stored in the current Kate session configuration."
msgstr ""
"Ciljni niz je skupina ukazov, ki jih je mogoče izvajati v določenem delovnem "
"imeniku. Nabore ciljev lahko dodate pod <guilabel>Projekti</guilabel> ali "
"<guilabel>Seja</guilabel>. Nabori ciljev po meri, dodani pod "
"<guilabel>Projekti</guilabel>, so shranjeni v datoteki <guilabel>."
"kateproject.build</guilabel> v korenskem imeniku projekta in se obnovijo, ko "
"se projekt ponovno odpre. Ciljni nizi, dodani pod <guilabel>Seja</guilabel>, "
"so shranjeni v trenutni konfiguraciji seje Kate."

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:628
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first row, in a target-set, contains a name for the set in column one, "
"and in column two we have the directory where the commands should be "
"executed. On each following row, we have a name for the command in column "
"one, a build command in column two and a run command in column three. To "
"edit one of these, double-click on the entry or use the edit shortcut (often "
"<keycap>F2</keycap>)."
msgstr ""
"Prva vrstica v ciljnem naboru vsebuje ime za nabor v stolpcu ena, v stolpcu "
"dva pa imamo imenik, kjer naj bi se izvajali ukazi. V vsaki naslednji "
"vrstici imamo ime za ukaz v stolpcu ena, ukaz za gradnjo v stolpcu dva in "
"ukaz za zagon v stolpcu tri. Če želite urediti eno od teh, dvokliknite vnos "
"ali uporabite bližnjico za urejanje (pogosto <keycap>F2</keycap>)."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:635 plugins.docbook:1803
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working Directory"
msgstr "Delovni imenik"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The second column of the first row in a target-set, is used to configure the "
"working directory used for compiling and running commands. If the project "
"plugin is enabled, the working directory string can also contain "
"placeholders for the project base directory path: <guilabel>%B</guilabel> "
"and name: <guilabel>%b</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"Drugi stolpec prve vrstice v ciljnem nizu se uporablja za konfiguracijo "
"delovnega imenika, ki se uporablja za prevajanje in izvajanje ukazov. Če je "
"projektni vtičnik omogočen, lahko niz delovnega imenika vsebuje tudi polja "
"za pot osnovnega imenika projekta: <guilabel>%B</guilabel> in ime: <guilabel>"
"%b</guilabel>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:643
#, no-c-format
msgid "Build Command"
msgstr "Ukaz Build"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The second column in the \"non-first rows\", contains the shell command to "
"run in the working directory. Note the word shell. Almost any shell command "
"will do. The build command can contain placeholders. <guilabel>%f</guilabel> "
"for the current file, <guilabel>%d</guilabel> for directory of the current "
"file and <guilabel>%n</guilabel> for the base-name of the current file (file "
"name without suffix)."
msgstr ""
"Drugi stolpec v \"neprvih vrsticah\" vsebuje shellov ukaz za zagon v "
"delovnem imeniku. Upoštevajte besedo lupina (shell). Skoraj vsak ukaz shella "
"bo ustrezal. Ukaz za gradnjo lahko vsebuje polja parametrov. <guilabel>%f</"
"guilabel> za trenutno datoteko, <guilabel>%d</guilabel> za imenik trenutne "
"datoteke in <guilabel>%n</guilabel> za osnovno ime trenutne datoteke (ime "
"datoteke brez pripone)."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:652
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run Command"
msgstr "Ukaz zagona"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:653
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The third column in the \"non-first rows\", can contain a shell command, for "
"execution in an actual terminal in the target-set working directory. The "
"terminal is opened as a tab. The plugin will try to reuse the terminal tab, "
"if the same command is executed and the previous application has exited."
msgstr ""
"Tretji stolpec v \"neprvih vrsticah\" lahko vsebuje shellov ukaz za izvedbo "
"v dejanskem terminalu v ciljno nastavljenem delovnem imeniku. Terminal se "
"odpre kot zavihek. Vtičnik bo poskušal znova uporabiti zavihek terminala, če "
"se izvede isti ukaz in se prejšnja aplikacija zapre."

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:661
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the top of the <guilabel>Target Settings</guilabel> tab, we have a "
"toolbar with a target filter and the following buttons:"
msgstr ""
"Na vrhu zavihka <guilabel>Ciljne nastavitve</guilabel> imamo orodno vrstico "
"s ciljnim filtrom in naslednjimi gumbi:"

#. Tag: member
