#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:4672
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4674
#, no-c-format
msgid "The plugin can be configured in two ways:"
msgstr "Vtičnik je mogoče konfigurirati na dva načina:"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4676
#, no-c-format
msgid "Globally, from the Configure dialog"
msgstr "Globalno v pogovornem oknu Konfiguriraj"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4677
#, no-c-format
msgid "On a per project basis using the <filename>.kateproject</filename> file"
msgstr ""
"Na podlagi posameznega projekta z uporabo datoteke <filename>.kateproject</"
"filename>"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4681
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When reading the config, the plugin will first try to read the config from "
"<filename>.kateproject</filename> file and then read the global config. "
"Example:"
msgstr ""
"Pri branju konfiguracije bo vtičnik najprej poskušal prebrati konfiguracijo "
"iz<filename>.kateproject</filename> in nato prebral globalno konfiguracijo. "
"Primer:"

#. Tag: screen
#: plugins.docbook:4685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"formatOnSave\": true,\n"
"    \"formatterForJson\": \"jq\",\n"
"    \"cmake-format\": {\n"
"        \"formatOnSave\": false\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"autopep8\": {\n"
"        \"formatOnSave\": false\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"{\n"
"    \"formatOnSave\": true,\n"
"    \"formatterForJson\": \"jq\",\n"
"    \"cmake-format\": {\n"
"        \"formatOnSave\": false\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"autopep8\": {\n"
"        \"formatOnSave\": false\n"
"    }\n"
"}"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4687
#, no-c-format
msgid "The above:"
msgstr "Zgoraj:"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4689
#, no-c-format
msgid "enables \"format on save\" globally"
msgstr "omogoča globalno \"formatiranje ob shranjevanju\""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4690
#, no-c-format
msgid "specifies \"jq\" as the formatter for JSON"
msgstr "določa \"jq\" kot oblikovalnika za JSON"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4691
#, no-c-format
msgid "disables \"format on save\" for cmake-format and autopep8"
msgstr "onemogoča \"formatiranje ob shranjevanju\" za cmake-format in autopep8"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4695
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To configure formatting for a project, first create a <filename>."
"kateproject</filename> file and then add a <code>\"formatting\"</code> "
"object to it. In the <code>\"formatting\"</code> object you can specify your "
"settings as shown in the previous example. Example:"
msgstr ""
"Če želite konfigurirati oblikovanje za projekt, najprej ustvarite <filename>."
"kateproject</filename> in nato dodajte temu predmet <code>\"formatting\"</"
"code>. V predmetu <code>\"formatting\"</code> lahko določite svoje "
"nastavitve, kot je prikazano v prejšnjem primeru. Primer:"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4698
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You need to enable the <link linkend=\"kate-application-plugin-projects"
"\">Project plugin</link> for this to work"
msgstr ""
"Omogočiti morate <link linkend=\"kate-application-plugin-projects\">Vtičnik "
"projekta</link>, da bo to delovalo"

#. Tag: screen
#: plugins.docbook:4700
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"name\": \"My Cool Project\",\n"
"    \"files\": [\n"
"        {\n"
"            \"git\": 1\n"
"        }\n"
"    ],\n"
"    \"formatting\": {\n"
"        \"formatterForJson\": \"clang-format\",\n"
"        \"autopep8\": {\n"
"            \"formatOnSave\": false\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"{\n"
"    \"name\": \"My Cool Project\",\n"
"    \"files\": [\n"
"        {\n"
"            \"git\": 1\n"
"        }\n"
"    ],\n"
"    \"formatting\": {\n"
"        \"formatterForJson\": \"clang-format\",\n"
"        \"autopep8\": {\n"
"            \"formatOnSave\": false\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}"

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:4705
#, no-c-format
msgid "Temporarily disable format on save"
msgstr "Začasno onemogoči formatiranje ob shranjevanju"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:4707
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While working you will often need to disable the formatting for a short "
"while due to any reason. You can do this from the menubar, "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Format on Save</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>. You can also trigger this action from the "
"<guilabel>Command bar</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Med delom boste pogosto morali zaradi različnih razlogov za kratek čas "
"onemogočiti oblikovanje. To lahko storite v menijski vrstici, "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Orodja</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Formatiranje ob "
"shranjevanju</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. To dejanje lahko sprožite tudi iz "
"<guilabel>Ukazne vrstice</guilabel>."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Similar to the example in the referenced section, the following "
#~ "configuration may be provided in a <literal>.kateproject</literal>. "
#~ "<screen>\n"
#~ "{\n"
#~ "    // this may also be an array of objects\n"
#~ "    \"exec\": {\n"
#~ "        \"hostname\": \"foobar\"\n"
#~ "        // the command could also be an array of string\n"
#~ "        \"prefix\": \"podman exec -i foobarcontainer\",\n"
#~ "        \"mapRemoteRoot\": true,\n"
#~ "        \"pathMappings\": [\n"
#~ "            // either of the following forms are possible\n"
#~ "            // a more automagic alternative exists as well, see "
#~ "referenced section\n"
#~ "            [ \"/dir/on/host\", \"/mounted/in/container\" ]\n"
#~ "            { \"localRoot\": \"/local/dir\", \"remoteRoot\": \"/remote/dir"
#~ "\" }\n"
#~ "        ]\n"
#~ "    },\n"
#~ "    \"dap\": {\n"
#~ "        \"debugpy\": {\n"
#~ "            \"run\": {\n"
#~ "                // in this section, it applies to all configurations\n"
#~ "                // this will match/join with the above object\n"
#~ "                \"exec\": { \"hostname\": \"foobar\" },\n"
#~ "                // if server is connected to,\n"
#~ "                // optionally specify explicit port (which is suitable "
#~ "published/forwarded)\n"
#~ "                \"port\": 5678,\n"
#~ "                // the server may then also have to accept more than "
#~ "localhost\n"
#~ "                \"host\": \"0.0.0.0\"\n"
#~ "            }\n"
#~ "        }\n"
#~ "    }\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ "</screen> The referenced section should be consulted for details, but in "
#~ "essence the <literal>prefix</literal> will be prepended before the DAP "
#~ "server command line specified elsewhere. The effect is that the server is "
#~ "run within the specified container and then in turn also the launched "
#~ "process. The <literal>pathMapping</literal> arranges for transformation "
#~ "of filepaths between editor's view and DAP server (container) view, e.g. "
#~ "when dealing with setting of breakpoints or handling of reported "
#~ "backtraces. Note that such mapping is optional and may or may not be "
#~ "useful. When dealing with C/C++ code that is compiled on \"host\", the "
#~ "symbol info references source files on host which do not exist at all in "
#~ "the other environment. However, in other scripted (e.g. python) "
#~ "circumstances, actual runtime files are referenced (on the other "
#~ "environment)."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Podobno kot v primeru v omenjenem razdelku je lahko naslednja "
#~ "konfiguracija podana v datoteki <literal>.kateproject</literal>. "
#~ "<screen>\n"
#~ "{\n"
#~ "    // this may also be an array of objects\n"
#~ "    \"exec\": {\n"
#~ "        \"hostname\": \"foobar\"\n"
#~ "        // the command could also be an array of string\n"
#~ "        \"prefix\": \"podman exec -i foobarcontainer\",\n"
#~ "        \"mapRemoteRoot\": true,\n"
#~ "        \"pathMappings\": [\n"
#~ "            // either of the following forms are possible\n"
#~ "            // a more automagic alternative exists as well, see "
#~ "referenced section\n"
#~ "            [ \"/dir/on/host\", \"/mounted/in/container\" ]\n"
#~ "            { \"localRoot\": \"/local/dir\", \"remoteRoot\": \"/remote/dir"
#~ "\" }\n"
#~ "        ]\n"
#~ "    },\n"
#~ "    \"dap\": {\n"
#~ "        \"debugpy\": {\n"
#~ "            \"run\": {\n"
#~ "                // in this section, it applies to all configurations\n"
#~ "                // this will match/join with the above object\n"
#~ "                \"exec\": { \"hostname\": \"foobar\" },\n"
#~ "                // if server is connected to,\n"
#~ "                // optionally specify explicit port (which is suitable "
#~ "published/forwarded)\n"
#~ "                \"port\": 5678,\n"
#~ "                // the server may then also have to accept more than "
#~ "localhost\n"
#~ "                \"host\": \"0.0.0.0\"\n"
#~ "            }\n"
#~ "        }\n"
#~ "    }\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ "</screen> Za podrobnosti glejte navedeni razdelek, vendar bo v bistvu "
#~ "predpona <literal>predpona</literal> dodana pred ukazno vrstico strežnika "
#~ "DAP, ki je navedena drugje. Učinek je, da se strežnik izvaja znotraj "
#~ "določenega vsebnika in nato tudi zagnani proces. <literal>pathMapping</"
#~ "literal> poskrbi za pretvorbo poti datotek med pogledom urejevalnika in "
#~ "pogledom strežnika DAP (vsebnika), npr. pri nastavljanju prekinitvenih "
#~ "točk ali obravnavi sporočenih povratnih sledi. Upoštevajte, da je takšno "
#~ "preslikavanje neobvezno in je lahko uporabno ali pa tudi ne. Pri delu s "
#~ "kodo C/C++, ki je prevedena na \"gostitelju\", se informacije o simbolih "
#~ "sklicujejo na izvorne datoteke na gostitelju, ki v drugem okolju sploh ne "
#~ "obstajajo. Vendar pa se v drugih okoliščinah skriptov (npr. python) "
#~ "sklicujejo na dejanske datoteke izvajalnega okolja (v drugem okolju)."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The following must evidently be kept in mind; <itemizedlist> <listitem> "
#~ "<para>The DAP server must be present in the environment/container, which "
#~ "must be configured to support proper debugger operation (so, if needed, "
#~ "privileged, capabilities). </para> </listitem> <listitem> "
#~ "<para>Communication between editor and DAP must be possible. In case of a "
#~ "container, the latter should either use host networking, or provide a "
#~ "suitable mapped/published port along with corresponding config snippet as "
#~ "in above example (as an auto-selected one in case of port 0 would not "
#~ "make it through). </para> </listitem> <listitem> <para> A specified "
#~ "executable/PID should be in \"container\" perspective, as well as any "
#~ "(debuggee executable) arguments. </para> </listitem> </itemizedlist> "
#~ "Also, as in the LSP case, some environment variables are set; "
#~ "<literal>KATE_EXEC_PLUGIN</literal> is set to <literal>dap</literal>, "
#~ "<literal>KATE_EXEC_SERVER</literal> is set to the debugger/language type "
#~ "(e.g. <literal>python</literal>) and <literal>KATE_EXEC_PROFILE</literal> "
#~ "is set to the configuration entry (e.g. <literal>launch</literal>)."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Očitno je treba upoštevati naslednje: <itemizedlist> <listitem> "
#~ "<para>Strežnik DAP mora biti prisoten v okolju/vsebniku, ki mora biti "
#~ "konfiguriran za podporo pravilnega delovanja razhroščevalnika (torej, če "
#~ "je potrebno, privilegirane zmogljivosti). </para> </listitem> <listitem> "
#~ "<para>Komunikacija med urejevalnikom in DAP mora biti mogoča. V primeru "
#~ "vsebnika mora slednji uporabljati omrežje gostitelja ali zagotoviti "
#~ "ustrezna preslikana/objavljena vrata skupaj z ustreznim delčkom "
#~ "konfiguracije, kot v zgornjem primeru (saj samodejno izbrana vrata v "
#~ "primeru vrat 0 ne bi šla skozi). </para> </listitem> <listitem> <para> "
#~ "Določena izvedljiva datoteka/PID mora biti v perspektivi \"vsebnika\", "
#~ "kot tudi vsi argumenti (izvedljive datoteke, iz katere se odpravlja "
#~ "napaka). </para> </listitem> </itemizedlist> Prav tako so, tako kot v "
#~ "primeru LSP, nastavljene nekatere spremenljivke okolja; "
#~ "<literal>KATE_EXEC_PLUGIN</literal> je nastavljen na <literal>dap</"
#~ "literal>, <literal>KATE_EXEC_SERVER</literal> je nastavljen na vrsto "
#~ "razhroščevalnika/jezika (npr. <literal>python</literal>) in "
#~ "<literal>KATE_EXEC_PROFILE</literal> je nastavljen na vnos konfiguracije "
#~ "(npr. <literal>launch</literal>)."

